						<div id="siteNotice"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>
						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Bertrand Meyer</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg/220px-Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg" width="220" height="147" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg/330px-Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg/440px-Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bertrand_Meyer_IMG_2481.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.23wmf18/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Bertrand Meyer</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Bertrand Meyer</b> (<span class="nowrap"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/ˈ/ primary stress follows" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">ˈ</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'m' in 'my'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">m</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/aɪər/ 'ire' in 'fire'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">aɪər</span></a></span><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span></span>; <small>French:&#160;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_French" title="Help:IPA for French">[mɛjɛʁ]</a></span>; born 1950 in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris" title="Paris">Paris</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/France" title="France">France</a>) is an academic, author, and consultant in the field of computer languages. He created the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eiffel_(programming_language)" title="Eiffel (programming language)">Eiffel programming language</a> and the idea of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_by_contract" title="Design by contract">design by contracts</a>.</p>
<p></p>
